# CSS: Tailwind-first, few globals

## Tailwind in TSX

Use **Tailwind utility classes** for standard layout and positioning: flex/grid, gap, padding/margin, alignment, sizing, overflow, z-index, visibility, responsive breakpoints.

```tsx
/* ❌ BAD — layout in component CSS */
<div className="panel">

/* ✅ GOOD */
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 p-6 min-h-0">
```

Do **not** add component `index.css` rules that only duplicate utilities (`display: flex`, `position: absolute`, `gap: 1rem`, etc.). Put those on the element in TSX.

## Global tokens: `src/index.css`

Define **few, heavily reused** design tokens in `src/index.css` (imported from `main.tsx`):

- **`@theme`** — colors, fonts, spacing scales exposed to Tailwind (`bg-app-bg`, `text-button-text`, etc.)
- **`:root`** — cross-component CSS variables consumed by component styles (`--frame-scale`, `--button-gap`, …)

Add a new global variable only when **multiple** components or Tailwind utilities need the same value. Prefer `@theme` tokens over ad-hoc `:root` names when Tailwind should own the name.

Do **not** scatter one-off globals in component CSS or page-level stylesheets.

## Component `index.css`

Colocate **non-trivial** styling in the component’s `index.css` (see `css-nested-classes` for class naming):

- Multi-layer backgrounds, masks, clip-paths, custom grids tied to assets
- Calculations from shared globals (`var(--frame-scale)`)
- Selectors that are awkward or noisy as long Tailwind class strings

Keep component files focused; use `@apply` sparingly for repeated utility bundles inside CSS (e.g. disabled states), not as a substitute for TSX layout.

```css
/* ✅ GOOD — custom frame geometry, shared tokens */
.button {
  --button-scale: calc(var(--frame-scale) * 0.7);
  display: grid;
  grid-template: /* … */;
}

.button:disabled {
  @apply cursor-not-allowed opacity-65;
}
```

## Decision checklist

| Need | Where |
|------|--------|
| Flex/grid, spacing, position in UI | Tailwind on TSX |
| App-wide color, font, spacing token | `src/index.css` `@theme` or `:root` |
| Asset-backed shape, nested block styling | Component `index.css` |

Reference: `src/index.css`, `src/components/Button/`.
